  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "i3hhY1Gj7i1CHc3+O3RJHFE7t9U=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:35.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Claim\nThe Swarm factory is registered at build time, but the GQL factory registration is deferred until after `buildModule()` completes, because it requires the reactor queue (which hosts the document-model resolver).\n\n## Evidence\nFrom the source: \"GQL is registered after build because `GqlRequestChannelFactory` needs the queue (for poll timer backpressure), which requires the document model resolver created inside `buildModule()`.\"\n\nThe wiring code shows this explicitly:\n\n```typescript\nconst module = await builder.buildModule();\nconst queue = module.reactorModule?.queue;\nif (queue) registerGqlFactory(queue);\n```\n\n## Why this ordering\n- Swarm's factory has no dependency on the queue, so it can be registered up front.\n- GQL's poll timer uses the queue to apply backpressure when the reactor is busy.\n- Attempting to register GQL before the queue exists would fail.\n\n## Source\nSwarm Channel Architecture, \"Wiring Into createBrowserReactor\" (createSwarmSyncBuilder note).",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:35.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:35.000Z"
    }
  },
